page.title: 10Local villages
page.content:
The main village in the block is Wiggenhall St.Germans (now usually called St.Germans) with - just across the river Great Ouse - a much smaller settlement called Wiggenhall St.Peter.
The village of Setchey is largely a commuter area for nearby towns (ribbon development along the main A10 trunk road), with a developing housing estate (owner occupiers) at the north-east corner of the block.
At the south-east is a very small hamlet - Tottenhill Row - which is a small collection of farm labourers' dwellings on a dirt road.
